Long.op.name: AR-L1196 - MULTIPHASE PRIMARY HEALTH CARE PROGRAM FOR MANAGING CHRONIC NONCOMMUNICABLE DISE
objectives: +Contribuir a la reducción de la morbimortalidad por enfermedades crónicas no transmisibles en Argentina, con énfasis en la población con cobertura pública exclusiva
Objective:
The objective of this second operation is to help reduce morbidity and mortality caused by chronic
noncommunicable diseases in Argentina, prioritizing the population with public coverage only. Specifically, this operation proposes to
help: (i) prioritize the primary care level as the gateway to the health care system; (ii) increase the population¿s access to screenings
for classification according to health risk; and (iii) increase access to timely treatment for those with moderate or high health risk suffering
from chronic conditions.

outcomes: Acceso/utilización de servicos hospitalarios incrementado
Long.op.name: BO-L1078 - Improved access to health services in Bolivia
objectives: +Reducción de la mortalidad materno - infantil en las redes de atención en salud en los Departamentos de La Paz y Potosí
Objective: The objective of the project is to improve the efficienc of health service production and the resolutive capacity of health networks in El Alto and Potosi to be able to attend to health requirements at the departmental level. The health networks will have greater capacity to resolve postponed or discouraged health needs, and will contribute to decongest reference hospitals at the national level. Given Bolivia's epidemilogical profile, the project's impact will be to contribute to the reduction of morbility and mortality, especially for mothers and infants. The project will complete and complement the functioning of health networks in Potosi and El Alto by constructing and equipping specialized hospitals in these cities.
outcomes_indicators: Egresos hospitalarios, por sexo (masculino) en los municipios de Potosí
outcomes_means: SNIS y registros administrativos de hospitales
outcomes_revised: Acceso/utilización de servicos hospitalarios incrementado

The health networks will have greater capacity to resolve postponed or discouraged health needs, and will contribute to decongest reference hospitals at the national level. Given Bolivia's epidemilogical profile, the project's impact will be to contribute to the reduction of morbility and mortality, especially for mothers and infants. The project will complete and complement the functioning of health networks in Potosi and El Alto by constructing and equipping specialized hospitals in these cities.

outcomes_revised: Estándar nacional de eficiencia de producción de servicios (egresos) cumplido

Long.op.name: BO-L1082 - Improved Access to Health Services El Alto Bolivia
objectives: +Reducción de la mortalidad: i) neonatal; ii) materna; y ii) por cáncer cervico-uterino en El Alto
Objective: The objective of the project is to increase the ability of the municipal health network to respond comprehensively and timely to a demand for health care for the city of El Alto and nearby rural areas in order to reduce mortality, particularly the maternal and morbidity and mortality from cervical cancer.

outcomes: 1. Calidad y Accesibilidad de los cuidados obstétricos, neonatales y de la Planificación Familiar, incrementada
Long.op.name: BO-L1198 - Program to improve accessibility to maternal and Neonatal health services in Bolivia
objectives: +Morbi-mortalidad materna y neonatal reducida
Objective: The program's general objective is to reduce maternal and neonatal morbidity and mortality, by increasingthe accessibility and enhancing the health outcomes of the prioritized health networks (those with the worst maternal and infantmortality and accessibility indicators). The specific objectives are: (i) to implement the essential neonatal obstetric care (ENOC)strategy and improve network performance by: (a) implementing processes for the continuous improvement of care quality, withemphasis on an ENOC service model; (b) supporting the digital transformation of the sector by improving health caremanagement information systems in the network and monitoring of maternal and neonatal morbidity and mortality; and(c) enhancing management capacities in the network and in individual healthcare facilities; and (ii) to strengthen the infrastructureof the health services network, by investing in works and equipment that improve its health outcomes, under a comprehensive,coordinated vision of the network
outcomes_indicators: Frecuentación hospitalaria (internamiento) (desagregado entre hombres y mujeres)
outcomes_means: Sistema Nacional de Información en Salud y Vigilancia Epidemiológica. SNIS-VE
outcomes_revised: Calidad y Accesibilidad de los cuidados obstétricos, neonatales y de la Planificación Familiar, incrementada

objectives: +Comportamientos de riesgo de la poblacion entre 15 y 29 años de edad en la ciudad de Fortaleza reducidos.

Long.op.name: BR-L1518 - Program to Strengthen the Care Model in the Paraiba Health Network
objectives: +Contribuir para a melhoria das condições de saúde da população da Paraíba
Objective: The general objective of the program is to contribute to improve the health conditions for the Paraiba population through the consolidation of the Health Care Networks and the strengthening of the State health management capacities.
outcomes_indicators: Cobertura de exames citopatológicos para detectar câncer de colo do útero (população recomendada pelo Ministério da Saúde)
outcomes_means: Fonte do indicador: SIA SUS/DATASUS. Fórmula: soma da frequência do número de exames citopatológicos do colo do útero (procedimentos 02.03.01.001-9, exames citopatológicos cervico vaginal / microflora e 02.03.01.008-6 exames citopatológicos cervico vaginal / microflora rastreamento) realizados em mulheres de faixa etária de 25 a 64 anos por município de residência e ano de atendimento População feminina na faixa etária de 25 a 64 anos no mesmo local e ano / 3
outcomes_revised: mediante la consolidación de las Redes Asistenciales de Salud (RAS)

Long.op.name: CO-L1248 - Program to improve sustainability of the health system in Colombia with an inclusive approach.
objectives: +Mejorar la sostenibilidad del SGSSS con el fin de preservar los logros obtenidos en materia de cobertura, equidad y protección financiera, así como mejorar la salud de la población
Objective: Improve sustainability of the SGSSS to preserve coverage, equity, and financial protection, as well as improve the population´s health. Long.op.name: DR-L1067 - Strengthening of the Management for Results of the Sector Health in Dominican Re
objectives: +Acceso de la población pobre a los servicios de salud mejorado y morbi-mortalidad materna e infantil disminuida
Objective: The overall project objective is to increase the efficiency and effectiveness of health spending allocated to the most vulnerable population of RD. The specific objectives are: (i) to improve the allocation of health spending by expanding the results-based financing, with special emphasis on primary care; (ii) contribute to decreased maternal morbidity and infant mortality by expanding strategy management improvements in health services in secondary and tertiary levels; y (iii) support the Ministry of Health in conducting sector through institutional strengthening and development of monitoring and evaluation tools for decision-making.
outcomes_indicators: Hospitales con SIGHO implementado y en funcionamiento en los hospitales en que se implementará el CEMI.
outcomes_means: Reportes anuales de evaluación emitidos por la Dirección de Tecnología de Información del MISPAS
outcomes_revised: mediante la expansión de una estrategia de mejoras gerenciales en los servicios de salud de segundo y tercer nivel

Long.op.name: DR-L1067 - Strengthening of the Management for Results of the Sector Health in Dominican Re
objectives: +Acceso de la población pobre a los servicios de salud mejorado y morbi-mortalidad materna e infantil disminuida
Objective: The overall project objective is to increase the efficiency and effectiveness of health spending allocated to the most vulnerable population of RD. The specific objectives are: (i) to improve the allocation of health spending by expanding the results-based financing, with special emphasis on primary care; (ii) contribute to decreased maternal morbidity and infant mortality by expanding strategy management improvements in health services in secondary and tertiary levels; y (iii) support the Ministry of Health in conducting sector through institutional strengthening and development of monitoring and evaluation tools for decision-making.
outcomes_indicators: Porcentaje de las muertes neonatales auditadas auditadas por los Comités de Maternidad Segura con al menos una de las medidas correctivas implementadas en los hospitales en que se implementará el CEMI.

outcomes: Improved quality of reproductive, maternal, and neonatal health services
Long.op.name: GY-L1058 - Support to Improve Maternal and Child Health
objectives: +Contribute to the reduction of maternal, perinatal, and neonatal deaths in Guyana by 2021
Objective: The operation will support among other activities: (i) quality improvements to maternal, neonatal, child, and reproductive health services at the primary as well as at the hospital level focusing on the areas with the highest concentrations of deaths: the focus here will also be on strengthening, among other strategies, Essential Neonatal Obstetrical Care (ENOC) and Emergency Obstetrical Neonatal Care (EONC); (ii) strengthening health service delivery capacity to increase coverage and use/demand for certain services and strengthen practices by the target population. Capacity building will also support the delivery of effective counseling services towards behavior change related to care-seeking for early prenatal and post-natal controls and attitudes towards institutional deliveries; and (iii) implementation of innovative financing schemes to overcome demand side barriers (such as transport related costs to access institutional delivery) faced by the targeted population and implementation of a reward system for improved performance by service providers
outcomes_indicators: Deliveries for which the partograph was used according to best practices.
outcomes_revised: Improved quality of reproductive, maternal, and neonatal health services

Long.op.name: GY-L1058 - Support to Improve Maternal and Child Health
objectives: +Contribute to the reduction of maternal, perinatal, and neonatal deaths in Guyana by 2021
Objective: The operation will support among other activities: (i) quality improvements to maternal, neonatal, child, and reproductive health services at the primary as well as at the hospital level focusing on the areas with the highest concentrations of deaths: the focus here will also be on strengthening, among other strategies, Essential Neonatal Obstetrical Care (ENOC) and Emergency Obstetrical Neonatal Care (EONC); (ii) strengthening health service delivery capacity to increase coverage and use/demand for certain services and strengthen practices by the target population. Capacity building will also support the delivery of effective counseling services towards behavior change related to care-seeking for early prenatal and post-natal controls and attitudes towards institutional deliveries; and (iii) implementation of innovative financing schemes to overcome demand side barriers (such as transport related costs to access institutional delivery) faced by the targeted population and implementation of a reward system for improved performance by service providers
outcomes_indicators: Institutional deliveries for which immediate neonatal care was provided to the infant according to the norms.
outcomes_revised: Improved quality of reproductive, maternal, and neonatal health services

outcomes: Improved quality of reproductive, maternal, and neonatal health services

Long.op.name: GY-L1058 - Support to Improve Maternal and Child Health
objectives: +Contribute to the reduction of maternal, perinatal, and neonatal deaths in Guyana by 2021
Objective: The operation will support among other activities: (i) quality improvements to maternal, neonatal, child, and reproductive health services at the primary as well as at the hospital level focusing on the areas with the highest concentrations of deaths: the focus here will also be on strengthening, among other strategies, Essential Neonatal Obstetrical Care (ENOC) and Emergency Obstetrical Neonatal Care (EONC); (ii) strengthening health service delivery capacity to increase coverage and use/demand for certain services and strengthen practices by the target population. Capacity building will also support the delivery of effective counseling services towards behavior change related to care-seeking for early prenatal and post-natal controls and attitudes towards institutional deliveries; and (iii) implementation of innovative financing schemes to overcome demand side barriers (such as transport related costs to access institutional delivery) faced by the targeted population and implementation of a reward system for improved performance by service providers
outcomes_indicators: Pregnant women with anemia at first antenatal visit.
outcomes_revised: Increased access and use of reproductive, maternal, and neonatal health services

outcomes: Extend coverage of diagnostic, medical consultation, and patient management services, inclusive of the country’s hinterlands, through digital health
Long.op.name: GY-L1080 - Health Care Network Strengthening in Guyana
objectives: +Improve the health of the Guyanese population through increased access, quality, and efficiency of health services
Objective: The objective is to improve the health of the Guyanese population through increased access, quality, and efficiency of health services. Specific objectives are: (i) improve health outcomes associated with low and high complexity procedures, by expanding the capacity of strategic hospitals; (ii) extend coverage of diagnostic, medical consultation, and patient management services, inclusive of the country's hinterlands, through digital health (DH); and (iii) increase the efficiency of the public health system, by strengthening key logistic, management, and support processes and inputs.
outcomes_indicators: Diabetic patients screened for diabetic retinopathy
outcomes_revised: Extend coverage of diagnostic, medical consultation, and patient management services, inclusive of the country’s hinterlands, through digital health

Objective: The objective is to improve the health of the Guyanese population through increased access, quality, and efficiency of health services. Specific objectives are: (i) improve health outcomes associated with low and high complexity procedures, by expanding the capacity of strategic hospitals; (ii) extend coverage of diagnostic, medical consultation, and patient management services, inclusive of the country's hinterlands, through digital health (DH); and (iii) increase the efficiency of the public health system, by strengthening key logistic, management, and support processes and inputs.
outcomes_indicators: Number of hospitals in the four targeted hinterland regions providing telehealth services (consultations and diagnostics)
outcomes_revised: Extend coverage of diagnostic, medical consultation, and patient management services, inclusive of the country’s hinterlands, through digital health

outcomes: Extend coverage of diagnostic, medical consultation, and patient management services, inclusive of the country’s hinterlands, through digital health

Specific objectives are: (i) improve health outcomes associated with low and high complexity procedures, by expanding the capacity of strategic hospitals; (ii) extend coverage of diagnostic, medical consultation, and patient management services, inclusive of the country's hinterlands, through digital health (DH); and (iii) increase the efficiency of the public health system, by strengthening key logistic, management, and support processes and inputs.
outcomes_indicators: Pregnant women that are screened for diabetes according to guidelines
outcomes_revised: Increase the efficiency of the public health system, by strengthening key logistic, management, and support processes and inputs

outcomes: To improve access to an upgraded and integrated primary and secondary health network in prioritized areas with an emphasis on chronic disease management
Long.op.name: JA-L1049 - Support for the Health Systems Strengthening for the Prevention and Care Management of Non-communicable Diseases Programme
objectives: +To improve access to an upgraded and integrated primary and secondary health network in prioritized areas with an emphasis on chronic disease management to provide more efficient and higher quality care.
Objective: The programme objective is to contribute to the improvement of the health of Jamaica's population by strengthening comprehensive policies for the prevention of Non-Communicable (Chronic) Diseases (NCDs)risk factors and improved access to an upgraded and integrated primary and secondary health network in prioritized areas with an emphasis on chronic disease management, that provide more efficient and higher quality care.The policy-based operation of this hybrid programme is the first of a programmatic policy-based loan series, which will be made up of two contractually independent and technically linked loans, as per document Policy-based Loans Guidelines for Preparation and Implementation (CS-3633-2).
outcomes_indicators: Ministry of Health equipment and facility maintenance budget
outcomes_means: Ministry of Finance and Public Service Expenditure Estimates
outcomes_revised: To improve access to an upgraded and integrated primary and secondary health network in prioritized areas with an emphasis on chronic disease management

Objective: The programme objective is to contribute to the improvement of the health of Jamaica's population by strengthening comprehensive policies for the prevention of Non-Communicable (Chronic) Diseases (NCDs)risk factors and improved access to an upgraded and integrated primary and secondary health network in prioritized areas with an emphasis on chronic disease management, that provide more efficient and higher quality care.The policy-based operation of this hybrid programme is the first of a programmatic policy-based loan series, which will be made up of two contractually independent and technically linked loans, as per document Policy-based Loans Guidelines for Preparation and Implementation (CS-3633-2).
outcomes_indicators: Ministry of Health equipment and facility maintenance budget
outcomes_means: Ministry of Finance and Public Service Expenditure Estimates
outcomes_revised: To improve access to an upgraded and integrated primary and secondary health network in prioritized areas with an emphasis on chronic disease management

outcomes: To improve access to an upgraded and integrated primary and secondary health network in prioritized areas with an emphasis on chronic disease management

Objective: The programme objective is to contribute to the improvement of the health of Jamaica's population by strengthening comprehensive policies for the prevention of Non-Communicable (Chronic) Diseases (NCDs)risk factors and improved access to an upgraded and integrated primary and secondary health network in prioritized areas with an emphasis on chronic disease management, that provide more efficient and higher quality care.The policy-based operation of this hybrid programme is the first of a programmatic policy-based loan series, which will be made up of two contractually independent and technically linked loans, as per document Policy-based Loans Guidelines for Preparation and Implementation (CS-3633-2).
outcomes_indicators: Ministry of Health equipment and facility maintenance budget
outcomes_means: Ministry of Finance and Public Service Expenditure Estimates
outcomes_revised: To improve access to an upgraded and integrated primary and secondary health network in prioritized areas with an emphasis on chronic disease management

outcomes: To improve access to an upgraded and integrated primary and secondary health network in prioritized areas with an emphasis on chronic disease management

Objective: The programme objective is to contribute to the improvement of the health of Jamaica's population by strengthening comprehensive policies for the prevention of Non-Communicable (Chronic) Diseases (NCDs)risk factors and improved access to an upgraded and integrated primary and secondary health network in prioritized areas with an emphasis on chronic disease management, that provide more efficient and higher quality care.The policy-based operation of this hybrid programme is the first of a programmatic policy-based loan series, which will be made up of two contractually independent and technically linked loans, as per document Policy-based Loans Guidelines for Preparation and Implementation (CS-3633-2).
outcomes_indicators: % of men age 18 years+ with hypertension that have their blood pressure controlled.
outcomes_revised: To provide more efficient and higher quality care for patients with chronic non-communicable diseases

outcomes: To provide more efficient and higher quality care for patients with chronic non-communicable diseases

Objective: The programme objective is to contribute to the improvement of the health of Jamaica's population by strengthening comprehensive policies for the prevention of Non-Communicable (Chronic) Diseases (NCDs)risk factors and improved access to an upgraded and integrated primary and secondary health network in prioritized areas with an emphasis on chronic disease management, that provide more efficient and higher quality care.The policy-based operation of this hybrid programme is the first of a programmatic policy-based loan series, which will be made up of two contractually independent and technically linked loans, as per document Policy-based Loans Guidelines for Preparation and Implementation (CS-3633-2).
outcomes_indicators: % of male students aged 13-15 years who smoke cigarettes

outcomes: Capacidades de oferta de servicios de salud mejoradas
Long.op.name: PE-L1228 - Program to Create Integrated Health Networks
objectives: +Calidad de los servicios en el primer nivel de atención mejorada
Objective: The objective of the program is to achieve adequate access for the population to timely,efficient, quality primary health services based on their needs. To this end, it proposes a reorganization of health service provider institutions (IPRESS) into integrated health networks to improve the effectiveness of the current care offering in metropolitan Lima and the priority regions of the country, and to enhance clinical support services in metropolitan Lima
outcomes_indicators: Porcentaje de usuarios de consulta externa que se sintieron “satisfechos” o “muy satisfechos” con la atención recibida
outcomes_means: Encuesta Nacional de Satisfaccion de usuarios de salud - SUSALUD
outcomes_revised: Capacidades de oferta de servicios de salud mejoradas

Long.op.name: PR-L1167 - Program to Strengthen Integrated and Comprehensive Health Services Networks based on Primary Health Care
objectives: +Contribuir a la mejora de las condiciones de salud de la población más vulnerable de Paraguay, a través del fortalecimiento de las RIISS basadas en Atención Primaria de Salud (APS).
Objective: The overall objective of the program is to help improve the health conditions of Paraguay's most vulnerable population by strengthening the Comprehensive, Integrated Health Services Networks (RIISS) based on primary care. The specific objectives are to: (i) expand and strengthen the care network, and (ii) boost the quality of priority lines of care, including mother and child health; essential obstetrics and neonatal care, particularly diabetes, hypertension, and cancer; and HIV/AIDS and tuberculosis.
outcomes_indicators: Porcentaje de Hospitalizaciones evitables en hombres

Long.op.name: PR-L1190 - Strengthening of the San Estanislao Hospital Services Network
objectives: +Mejorar el estado de salud de la población priorizada por medio de la extensión de la accesibilidad y cobertura efectiva de servicios de salud de calidad
Objective: Is to improve the health status of the prioritized population through the extension of accessibility and effective coverage of quality health services. The specific objectives are: (i) to increase the resolution capacity of the supply of second- and third-level health services; and (ii) increase the efficiency and quality of care processes.

objectives: +Mejorar el estado de salud de la población priorizada por medio de la extensión de la accesibilidad y cobertura efectiva de servicios de salud de calidad
Objective: Is to improve the health status of the prioritized population through the extension of accessibility and effective coverage of quality health services. Long.op.name: TT-L1039 - Health Services Support Program
objectives: +Lifestyle diseases management among adults improved
Objective: The objective of the Health Services Support Program (HSSP) is to prevent and control risk factors and non-communicable diseases among adults, and primary and secondary school students by strengthening the delivery of integrated primary care services; implementing behavior change programs and policies; improving health information management; ensuring adequate Human Resources for Health (HRH); and enhancing health facilities investment management through the innovative application and use of information and communication technology (ICT) including hardware, software, people, data and network

Objective: The objective of the Health Services Support Program (HSSP) is to prevent and control risk factors and non-communicable diseases among adults, and primary and secondary school students by strengthening the delivery of integrated primary care services; implementing behavior change programs and policies; improving health information management; ensuring adequate Human Resources for Health (HRH); and enhancing health facilities investment management through the innovative application and use of information and communication technology (ICT) including hardware, software, people, data and network

Long.op.name: UR-L1161 - Program to Strengthen the Management of ASSE
objectives: +Mejorar la efectividad y eficiencia de la producción de servicios públicos de salud
Objective: The general objective of the program is to help make the production of public health services in Uruguay more effective and efficient. Specifically, the program would support the production and use of timely, reliable, and homogeneous information for decision-making by the healthcare and executing units of the Government Health Services Administration (ASSE), as well as the ASSE's central administration, the Ministry of Economy and Finance, and the Ministry of Public Health.
outcomes_indicators: Unidades asistenciales que consultan al menos 3 veces al año los Tableros de Gestion del Sistema de Información Gerencial
outcomes_means: Sistema de Información Gerencial de ASSE
